Text.Value: Hey. That's close enough. You ain't no Harper and you ain't no Fist. Don't need the likes of you crashing our party.
She's inside - one of the ground floor chambers.
Good. Wouldn't want to get it wrong in your eulogy.
If you're serious, go talk to his aide, Florrick. She's inside, 'strategising'.
Nah. Mind flayers don't really have names.
Bastards torched the pig-sty we were staying in and made off with the Grand Duke of Baldur's Gate himself.
Ah the Flaming Fist. You don't like people like me, do you?
Hey. That's close enough. Artefact or no, I don't like the likes of you crashing our party.
See? Help needed, help offered.
Shut up. And you, keep walking.

EditorData.NodeContext: The 'shut up' is aimed at Ulthred - 'And you, keep walking' is at the player. Both Ulthred and the player behaved antagonistically towards one another.

Text.Value: You got a name?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) Ulthred keeps looking you in the eyes and smiles before he speaks.
EditorData.NodeContext: Ulthred keeps looking you in the eyes and smiles before he speaks with menace.

Text.Value: Yeah. I'm touched.
Daisy Dewdrop Fluffington.
Good. Wouldn't want to piss on the wrong grave come the morrow.
Give it a rest, Ulthred. We need all the godsdamned help we can get.
Florrick's here? Where can I find her?

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Said to the Flaming Fist, not the player.

Text.Value: A bit on edge, my arse!
A rescue party sounds right up my alley as a matter of fact.
We're waiting for orders. Jaheira's and the counsellor's. Florrick is Ravengard's political advisor - and sore as a snakebite about losing him, too.
No bother - I'm used to Flaming Fists being impotent arse-wipes.
Don't worry - I'm used to pricks in a uniform being rude.
Move along, godsdammit. Bloody freaks everywhere.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: (Cine) He’s genuinely taken aback by the player’s response and takes a step back. He’s afraid.
EditorData.NodeContext: He’s genuinely taken aback by the player’s response and takes a step back. He’s afraid.

Text.Value: Not that you'll give a triple-shat damn, but we were ambushed by them bloody cultists.
Well - good luck with all that.
What party is it that I'm crashing?
Say no more. Saving dukes is one of my specialties.
Come on. We need to talk to Florrick.
I usually say 'The Dark Urge', but I've been workshopping 'The Sleepless Knife' and 'The Death Dream'.
Rescue party.
So what are you standing around here for?
Much obliged, worms-for-brains.
I expected a bit more decorum from a Flaming Fist soldier.
I was there in the aftermath. I don't suppose Counsellor Florrick made it all the way here?
Glare at Ulthred.
Sure did, for all the good that does us.
Because my bath hasn't run yet, why do you think?
Want me to shine your boots while I'm at it?
Easy. He's a bit on edge since the, uh... incident.
Guess you need to be a godsdamned counsellor to get room and board around here.
The Absolute's taken him, then - no question about it.
Yes. [GEN_PlayerName_c11eee1e-7815-6143-7233-f2427799fa53].

Synopsis: Two guards standing by a fountain, one a long-lived gnome Harper and one a rough-and-ready Flaming Fist human. The Fist is on edge and none too friendly, the Harper is calmer and more forthcoming.
